Title : Tri Martolod
Text : '''''Tri Martolod''''' ("Three sailors" in [[Breton language|Breton]]) or '''''Tri Martolod Yaouank''''' ("Three young sailors"), is a [[Music of Brittany|traditional Breton song]] which dates to the 18th century in [[Lower Brittany]]. It was made famous by the interpretation, the arrangement and the recordings made by the Breton [[celtic harp|harpist]] [[Alan Stivell]], in the 1970s.

The lyrics tell the story of three young sailors who embark for [[Newfoundland]] and the history quickly settles into a romantic dialogue. The music is a [[round (music)|round]] in three steps typical of the South [[Cornouaille]] and common in the [[Brittany|Breton coastal areas]].

